args: Three hundred years ago, in a settlement\nravaged by an imperial invasion...
Heh heh heh. You gave us some trouble\nthere, friend, but you're cornered now.
To think a human would dare...

Bwaa ha ha ha! And to think that YOU,
a mighty dragon, would fall like this!
It's time for us to free the world from
the clutches of you arrogant wyrms!
Wait, is that lightning? What the...\nGYAAAAAAAAH!
Who are the arrogant ones here, hmm?\n...Are you all right, my brother?
Heard of me, have you? How delightful!

But yes, the proud ruler of thunderclouds
has been pandering to the humans and
aiding them in a fierce battle—or so say
the latest rumors, at least.
I'm actually not ACTIVELY pandering.\nI just happen to find them intriguing and\nwanted a front-row seat to their goings-on.
While I thank you for saving me,\nLightwyrm, I cannot consent to your ways.\nYou must stop aiding the humans at once.

Do you not see this land? Their folly has
turned the waters stagnant, befouled the
soil, and polluted the winds. Such actions
cannot be suffered to stand!
I hate the humans, and can never forgive\nthe horrors they have wrought. As a fellow\ndragon, surely you must understand this!
Oh, I absolutely see why you'd think that\nif you only consider the Empire types. But...
The present day, in a city of commerce built up by\nthe countless folk coming and going in its streets.
Goodness, but three centuries of time\ncertainly do change a place. To think this\nused to be that broken-down little hamlet!
The city's being attacked by a dragon!
My hatred for humans burns my very soul,\nand I will hold back no longer!
Hey, bucko! Why the hell are ya attackin'\nthe city?! What'd it ever do to you?!
Please calm down and tell us what\nhappened. Maybe we can help.
I have waited three hundred years for your\nkind to reflect upon their misdeeds and show\nnature its due respect.
But you have NOT changed! Your ugly\nconflicts continue apace, and it is we\ndragons who suffer for them!
Now hold on just a hot minute there!\nIt's the Empire who's causing you all\nthat trouble, and the Empire alone.
The political bundling of your kinds is no\nconcern of mine. My fury comes for all!
I don't want to fight, but...
You waited the full three hundred years?\nNow THAT'S discipline!
Do you know this dragon, Jupiter?!
I helped him out three centuries ago when\nhe was being attacked by the Empire.
He was yelling about the same kinds of\nthings all the way back then, so I stepped\nin to help smooth things over.
I hate the humans, and can never forgive\nthe horrors they have wrought. As a fellow\ndragon, surely you must understand this!
Oh, I absolutely see why you'd think that\nif you only consider the Empire types. But...
While they might be foolish now, I think\nit's a tad premature to start employing\nthe forceful hand now.

Compared to we dragons, people are little
more than babies. And just as you wouldn't
expect perfection from an infant, so too
should we expect them to still be growing.
Be they adult or babe, I will not turn\na blind eye to those who do harm.
A fair point. So how about this?\nIn exchange for my having saved you,\nplease give them a little more time.

Let's see... A hundred years is too short,
and I'll get bored of waiting if we go to
five, so what say we split the difference
at three hundred years?
After all, three centuries is but an eyeblink\nto us dragons, right?
And what happens if I wait?

We'll have new generations of people,
the trends of the times will shift, and the
state of things will change for the better!
...Or that's my hope, at least.

That's because I don't know the future,
which is what makes it so interesting.
Certainly more interesting than killing
all of them here and now, no?
Very well. I will give them three centuries.\nBut if they fail to grow and learn, do not\nexpect me to show any mercy.
Then I'll see you in a while!
...I did as you bade, Lightwyrm, and waited\nthree hundred years to see if people could\nreform themselves. They did not.
They have not changed in these years.\nThey destroy nature, make us suffer,\nand fight with unspeakable violence!
No excuses! I will not hear it!
I don't think we're talkin' our way\noutta this one.
Hmm... I see. There's certainly some truth\nto what you say.
I'm sorry, {player_name},\nbut I'm taking his side on this.
From now on, I am your enemy!
